text: Bushnell is an unincorporated community in Barton County, in the U.S. state of Missouri. ==History== A post office called Bushnell was established in 1888, and remained in operation until 1901. The community was named after its founder, Andy Bushnell. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Barton County, Missouri Category:Unincorporated communities in Missouri
title: Bushnell, Missouri
